    "Angled towards cinematography we find work such as Roto++ (Li et al. 2016) -a rotoscoping tool with the ambition of respecting the artists' requirements.",
    "Roto++ improves upon traditional interpolation techniques by combining a real-time appearance tracking and a novel shape manifold regularization process (built on the Gaussian process latent variable model (GP-LVM) (Lawrence and Hyvärinen 2005)).",
    "Subsequently, within a sequence of frames the method (1) predicts the change of a shape manifold and (2) identifies which next keyframe needs to be manually roto scoped.",
